{"session_id":"svc-1778088404214854202","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-06T17:26:46.316208005Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-8fa7ecf6-20260506T172641-48134d22","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260506T172641-48134d22/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260506T172641-48134d22/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260506T172641-48134d22/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260506T172641-48134d22/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260506T172641-48134d22/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-8fa7ecf6\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003etry: preflight execution resources before claim and worktree setup\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;ddx try can claim/checkpoint and then fail during worktree setup when the temp worktree or evidence root is out of bytes/inodes or unwritable. In the May 6 incident, git worktree add failed with No space left on device after creating partial execution artifacts, and the failure was treated as ordinary execution_failed instead of a resource guardrail.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:686-714 creates the temp worktree parent, commits/checkpoints, resolves base, and calls WorktreeAdd before any resource-health check of $TMPDIR/ddx-exec-wt or .ddx/executions/.ddx/runs.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:713-714 returns immediately on WorktreeAdd failure, so partial unregistered directories can remain outside the deferred WorktreeRemove path.\u0026#xA;- cli/cmd/try.go:306-342 routes ddx try through ExecuteBeadWorker without a pre-claim resource gate that can fail before claiming the target bead.\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md:454-467 requires ddx try to validate roots, run one cleanup pass, re-check, and return resource_exhausted without claiming when still unhealthy.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Introduce a resource checker abstraction that validates temp worktree root and durable evidence root writability, free bytes, and free inodes where supported.\u0026#xA;- Run resource preflight before claim/worktree creation in ddx try paths, using the cleanup manager once before final failure.\u0026#xA;- Classify persistent resource failure as resource_exhausted with structured detail, not generic execution_failed/quota.\u0026#xA;- Ensure WorktreeAdd failure removes partial unregistered worktree directories created for the attempt.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Do not decide ddx work loop stop behavior here; sibling ddx work bead consumes the resource_exhausted outcome.\u0026#xA;- Do not add background cleanup cadence here.\u0026#xA;- Do not implement a real low-disk integration test that fills a filesystem; use injectable resource checker/fake filesystem boundaries.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. TestTryResourcePreflight_FailsBeforeClaim verifies a failing injected resource checker runs cleanup once, returns resource_exhausted, and leaves the bead open/unclaimed.\u0026#xA;2. TestTryResourcePreflight_RechecksAfterCleanup verifies ddx try proceeds when cleanup restores healthy resource status.\u0026#xA;3. TestExecuteBeadWorktreeAddFailure_RemovesPartialDir verifies a simulated WorktreeAdd ENOSPC failure removes the attempt partial directory under DDX_EXEC_WT_DIR.\u0026#xA;4. TestTryResourcePreflight_ChecksEvidenceAndTempRoots verifies both the temp worktree root and durable evidence root are checked for writability and resource health.\u0026#xA;5. Production ddx try/work paths call the resource preflight before claim/worktree creation; tests assert the new code path is wired, not just unit-tested.\u0026#xA;6. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run \u0026#34;TestTryResourcePreflight|TestExecuteBeadWorktreeAddFailure\u0026#34; -count=1 passes.\u0026#xA;7. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:agent, area:cli, kind:bug, reliability, spec:FEAT-010, spec:SD-025, cleanup, resource-exhaustion\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-f3dfde0d\" spec-id=\"FEAT-010\" base-rev=\"e80b36ad1aaa5331188a29e92bd351165478fd18\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260506T172641-48134d22\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-010\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md\"\u003eFeature: Task Execution\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260506T172641-48134d22","base_rev":"e80b36ad1aaa5331188a29e92bd351165478fd18","bead_id":"ddx-8fa7ecf6","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260506T172641-48134d22","correlation_id":"ddx-8fa7ecf6:20260506T172641-48134d22","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260506T172641-48134d22/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"5c7d273a9ac3c448d6d6acfcdc5c2116a3858efd25c0acf3ca85e50d2b56b0a3","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-5cfe43e4","worker_id":""}}}
